<p><strong>QUOTE</strong></p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-key adv <span class="nt">--keyserver</span> hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 <span class="nt">--recv</span> 2930ADAE8CAF5059EE73BB4B58712A2291FA4AD5
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">"deb [ arch=amd64,arm64 ] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu xenial/mongodb-org/3.6 multiverse"</span> | <span class="nb">sudo tee</span> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.6.list
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get update
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get <span class="nb">install</span> <span class="nt">-y</span> mongodb-org
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This will install the most stable version of mongod, 3.6 at time of writing. If you want to install a different version please refer to the <a href="https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/">link</a> above.</p>

